text: Gasherbrum V is a mountain in the Karakoram range, in Pakistan. It was thought to be part of Gasherbrum IV until 1934. The first people to reach the top were Seong Nak-jong and Ahn Chi-young, in 2014. == References == Category:Karakoram Category:Mountains of Gilgit-Baltistan
title: Gasherbrum V
